  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\n<!--A clear and concise description of what the bug is and steps to reproduce it.-->\r\n\r\nUnder Lodestar 1.2.1, metric beacon_finalized_epoch returns the current epoch and not the finalized epoch.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\n<!--A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen.-->\r\n\r\nbeacon_finalized_epoch should return the finalized epoch.\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n\r\n1. Go to metrics page at port 8008\r\n2. Search for \"beacon_finalized_epoch\" metric\r\n3. Compare value to known finalized epoch from a source such as beaconcha.in or another consensus client.\r\n4. beacon_finalized_epoch is actually showing the current epoch and not the finalized epoch.\r\n\r\nPersonally, I would welcome a new beacon_current_epoch metric alongside the beacon_finalized_epoch metric.\r\n",
